@mosquito do I understand correctly that this does not relates to a robust connection and it is necessary here to just correctly handle connection closing (not to continue message publishing in this case)?
https://github.com/mosquito/aio-pika/blob/53f29221033077fe98ea3b657003f060f6a5c06c/aio_pika/channel.py#L208-L210
I turned my attention to it because we cannot reuse the same channel to publish a message after reconnect (within a robust connection): `aio_pika.channel.Channel.initialize` cannot obtain `_write_lock` as it already gained by `aio_pika.channel.Channel._publish`.

If a data-attribute is undefined, jQuery will return an empty string... so this is also possible:

```js
textExtraction: function(node, table)
{
    return node.textContent + ' ' + $(node).attr('data-tags');
},
```

If the data-attribute is undefined, the extra space at the end will get stripped out when the data is cached.

Hmm, ok I may not need to change anything internally if a simple change to that code is made. Essentially, don't remove the `thead` and `tbody` from the table.

In this ([updated demo](http://jsfiddle.net/xg6ysrpk/3/)), I've included the [`parser-input-select.js`](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/parsers/parser-input-select.js) file to add the checkbox parser and extra code to highlight the row when checked. It does not include code for a checkbox in the thead.

```js
$(function () {

	// column containing all of the checkboxes (zero-based index)
	var checkboxColumn = 0,
	// resort the table after the checkbox status has changed
	resort = true,

	$t = $('table');

	$t.on('change.tisc mouseup.tisc', 'thead input[type=checkbox]', function () {
		c = this.checked;
		$t.find('tbody tr:visible td:nth-child(' + (checkboxColumn + 1) + ') input').each(function () {
			this.checked = c;
		});
		// update all checkboxes at once
		$t.trigger('update');
	});

	//if any checkbox is unchecked, uncheck the checkAll box
	$t.on('change.tisc', 'input[type=checkbox]', function () {
		if (!this.checked) { //if any checkbox is unchecked
			$t.find('thead th:eq(' + checkboxColumn + ') input[type=checkbox]').prop('checked', false);
		}
	});



	$('table').tablesorter({
		theme: 'blue',
		widgets: ['zebra', 'stickyHeaders', 'filter'],
		headers: {
			0: {
				sorter: 'checkbox'
			}
		}
	});

	function addHeaderRow(table) {
		table.append('<tr><th><input type="checkbox"></th>' +
			'<th>AlpaNumeric</th><th>Numeric</th><th>Animals</th>' +
			'<th>Sites</th></tr>');
	}

	function addBodyRows(table, row) {
		table.append('<tr role="row"><td><input type="checkbox"></td>' +
			'<td>abc 123</td><td>10</td><td>Koala</td><td>http://www.google.com</td>' +
			'</tr>');
		table.append('<tr role="row"><td><input type="checkbox"></td>' +
			'<td>abc 1</td><td>10</td><td>Koala</td><td>http://www.google.com</td>' +
			'</tr>');
	}

	$('#updateTable').click(function () {
		var table = $('table');
		// empty thead (preserves thead/tbody elements)
		table.find('thead, tbody').empty();
		// remove all tbodies
		table.find('tbody:gt(0)').remove();

		addHeaderRow(table.find('thead'));
		addBodyRows(table.find('tbody'));

		// updateAll because the thead content has changed
		table.trigger('updateAll', [resort]);

	});

});
```

By the way, you can save yourself a lot of headache/work by adding a class name to your headers:

```html
<th class="select2">AlphaNumeric</th>
<th class="select2">AlphaNumeric 2</th>
<th>Numeric</th>
<th class="select2">Animals</th>
<th>Sites</th>
```

then instead of defining the `filterFormatter` by column index, just use the class name ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/abkNM/5043/)):

```js
filter_formatter: {
	// target all select2 columns
	'.select2' : function ($cell, indx) {
		return $.tablesorter.filterFormatter.select2($cell, indx, {
			tags: true,
			tokenSeparators: [',', ' ', '|'],
			//separator: "|",
			match: true // adds "filter-match" to header
		});
	}
}
```

