@nlagaros @relevitt I will comment on that PR shortly, but the short version of the reply is that I find that the parallel implementation in the same module doesn't do anything good for readability of an already complicated module and I do not like the idea of pulling twisted in as a general dependency, so I would not favor that PR.

What I could support however, is an implementation in another module, say `events_twisted` with a similar interface. That would allow us to keep the simpler implementation in both modules and make the twisted dependency optional, by catching import errors and formatting an easy to understand exception that twisted will need to be installed separately. The downside to this is of course that someone will need to take ownership of this module and port improvements.

In general, I would also really like it if the bugs that you have with the ordinary implementation and reported and kept updated, so that hopefully they can be fixed in the future.

