On Windows and Linux the hashing works OK in the coordinate encoder (produces matching long integer seed's for Random). But as you've seen can be problematic if hashing text files (regardless of encoding, UTF-8/16 etc.). The difference with text files being the alternative ```\r\n``` and ```\n``` line endings on different OS. Python does a really good job shielding users from line ending and path separator differences internally.
Valuable to have some more Random checks, that include 32 and 64 bit version.

