@ogrisel This minimal example should raise an AssertionError on Python 2.7. It looks like the problem arises from an interaction between metaclasses and inheritance causing some objects to try to be pickled more than once.

```python
class Meta(object):
    def __new__(mcl, name, *args, **kwargs):
        ret = type(name, (Subclass,), kwargs)
        return ret

class Subclass(Meta):
    pass

class f(Subclass):
    __metaclass__ = Meta

import cloudpickle
cloudpickle.dumps(f)
# AssertionError
```

